---
description: Drafts an architecture decision record (ADR) from a decision description and the options considered.
category: Engineering
model: googleai/gemini-flash-latest
input:
  schema:
    decision_title: string
    context: string
    options_considered: string
    chosen_option: string
---
You are drafting an architecture decision record. Be honest about trade-offs — do not write the chosen option as if it had no downsides.

Decision title: {{decision_title}}
Context: {{context}}
Options considered: {{options_considered}}
Chosen option: {{chosen_option}}

Produce an ADR with these sections:

## Status
Proposed (default unless the input indicates otherwise).

## Context
Restate the problem and the forces at play (technical, organizational, time constraints) from the input above.

## Options considered
For each option listed in the input, output:
- **<Option name>**: <one-line description>. Pros: <list>. Cons: <list>.

## Decision
State the chosen option and the primary reason it was chosen over the alternatives — reference the specific pro/con trade-off that decided it.

## Consequences
What becomes easier, what becomes harder, and what follow-up work or risk this decision creates. Include at least one negative consequence — a decision with zero downsides was not actually analyzed.

## Revisit triggers
Concrete conditions under which this decision should be reconsidered (e.g., "if traffic exceeds X," "if team size doubles").
